The course provides an overview of the management of archaeological fieldwork, the requirements for conducting fieldwork and the obligations of the archaeologist. Students take a part of pre- and post-fieldwork processes as well as conducting archaeological surveys or excavations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the methods used in the archaeological fieldwork and to teach their application in practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the completion of the course, the student will be able to independently manage archaeological fieldwork. The student has acquired the knowledge of methodology and the practical skills to conduct an archaeological survey or excavations. The student will be aware of the legal requirements for an excavation application and research design as well as the requirements for systematizing and archiving excavations data, artefacts and ecofacts. The student will also be aware of archaeological ethics and safety during fieldwork
